# ──────────────────────────────── 80 chars ───────────────────────────────────┤


# Commit Message Format
# =====================
#
# Each commit message consists of a header, a body, and a footer.
#
# <header>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <body>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <footer>
#
# The header is mandatory. The body is mandatory for all commits except those
# of type "docs"; when present it must be at least 20 characters long. The
# footer is optional. No line may exceed 80 characters.
#
# Commit Message Header
# ---------------------
#
# ```
# <type>(<scope>)[!]: <short summary>
#   │       │     │             │
#   │       │     │             └─⫸ Summary in present tense. Not capitalized.
#   │       │     │                  No period at the end.
#   │       │     │
#   │       │     └─⫸ Optional "!" after scope indicates a BREAKING CHANGE
#   │       │
#   │       └─⫸ Commit Scope: derived from the changed files (a stablehlo/
#   │                         subdir — api|conversions|dialect|integrations|
#   │                         reference|tests|transforms), or a blessed alias
#   │                         (vhlo|refine|...). See .fractal-commit-lint.toml.
#   │
#   └─⫸ Commit Type: build|chore|ci|docs|feat|fix|perf|refactor|style|test
# ```
#
# Use the imperative, present tense in the summary and body: "fix" not "fixed"
# nor "fixes". Explain the motivation for the change — why, not what.
#
# Commit Message Footer
# ---------------------
#
# The footer can contain breaking-change / deprecation notes and issue
# references:
#
# ```
# BREAKING CHANGE: <summary>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <description + migration instructions>
# <BLANK LINE>
# Fixes #<issue number>
# ```
#
# Revert commits begin with `revert: ` followed by the reverted header, and the
# body contains `This reverts commit <SHA>` plus the reason.
